definition: celestial soldier/(old) imperial troops/(Tw, jocular) clumsy army recruit/(more generally) bungler/screw-up
celestial troops and generals (idiom)/fig. superior forces

sentences.english: And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host, praising God and saying.
sentences.chinese: 忽然有一大队天兵同向那天使赞美神说。

sentences.english: The ancients thought its jagged peaks resembled gods and heavenly guardians .
sentences.chinese: 古人认为它嶙峋的尖峰就像神仙和天兵。

sentences.english: None of the heavenly generals and soldiers could do anything about it.
sentences.chinese: 没有任何天兵天将能够阻止它。

sentences.english: The Jade Emperor was enraged, and ordered the heavenly generals and their troops to arrest the four dragons.
sentences.chinese: 玉帝勃然大怒，而命令了天兵天将拘捕四龙。

definition: celestial troops and generals (idiom)/fig. superior forces
Temple in Heaven (e.g. of the Jade Emperor)
lower bound (math.)/world of mortals/(of Gods) to descend to the world of mortals
same as 閻羅王|阎罗王/Yama, King of Hell/translation of Sanskrit: Yama Raja
